==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Culvert
<hw>Cul"vert</hw> <pr>(k?l"v?rt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. from
OF. <ets>coulouere</ets>, F. <ets>couloir</ets>, channel, gutter,
gallery, fr. <ets>couler</ets> to flow. See <er>Cullis</er>.]</ety>
<def>A transverse drain or waterway of masonry under a road, railroad,
canal, etc.; a small bridge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

